article.headline: Long Island U. 70, Canisius 63
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Kyle Johnson scored 18 points, Kellen Allen added 16 and LIU rallied for a 70-63 victory over winless Canisius on Saturday night. Eugene Kotorobai added 12 points for the Blackbirds (3-1), who trailed 37-27 at the half. Willie Hassell led the Griffins (0-4) with 19 points. Frank Tulner and Jovan Robinson each added 11. Robinson scored all of all his 11 points, including three 3-pointers, in the first half as Canisius built a 10-point halftime lead. A layup by Julius Coles gave the Griffins their largest lead of the game, 47-31, with 16:07 left. LIU responded with a 34-9 run behind Johnson's 13 points to take a 65-56 lead with 4:09 remaining. Canisius got as close as 67-63 on Tulner's jumper at 1:07
